r to gain media attention, but also in making these experts themselves “look longer” to understand more fully. Ideal for researchers who want a foothold for presenting and preparing their work for conferences, journal publications, and funding agencies, the book explains four tools that all readers can use—a phone, a camera, a scanner, and a microscope—and then offers important advice on composition and image manipulation ethics. The Visual Elements—Photography is an essential element in any scientist’s, engineer’s, or photographer’s library.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aPhotographyxScientific applicationsvHandbooks, manuals, etc. 0aPhotography-Scientific applications. 0aVisual communication in sciencevHandbooks, manuals, etc. 0aVisual communication in science. 7aPhotography / General.2bisacsh  acamera, phone, microscope, scanner, images, pictures, library, Engineering, science, technology, grant applications, communication, courses, research, journal publications, conferences, composition, media, art, artist, gallery, national geographic.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311079732940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226827032423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226827032/original  a978-3-11-079732-9  University of Chicago Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  aGBV-deGruyter-alles